Java allows exceptions for flow of control. This is done by the JRE runtime itself in APIs like `Double.parseDouble` via a `NumberFormatException` and `Paths.get` via a `InvalidPathException`. 

Given you&#39;ve written a component that validates Number strings for `Double.ParseDouble`, maybe using a Regex, maybe a hand-written parser, or perhaps something that embeds some other domain rules that restricts the range of a double to something specific, how best to test this component? I think an obvious test would be to assert that, when the resulting string is parsed, no exception is thrown. I would write that test using either the above `assertDoesNotThrow` or `/*comment*/{code}` block. Something like


